sentences: Brann Timothy Dailor  (born March 19, 1975) is an American drummer and singer, best known as a member of heavy metal band Mastodon, in which he is the drummer and one of three vocalists.
Dailor first started playing in a band called Evisceration from 1991 to 1993, when the band broke up.
In 2015, Dailor announced his side project called Arcadea.
Dailor appeared in a balloon suit from OppoSuits at the 2015 Grammys.
Dailor appeared on a 2018 episode of the History Channel reality show Counting Cars called "Heavy Metal Caddy" in which he had his 1970 Cadillac Coupe DeVille restored.

Dailor's main influence is Phil Collins of Genesis in its 1970s era.
Dailor was also a founding member of mathcore band Lethargy, and the progressive rock/funk metal band Gaylord and played with Today Is the Day.

As previously reported, the band's original song "White Walker" is featured on the Game of Thrones mixtape Catch the Throne Vol. 2, but in the instance of their physical appearance, a press release from Reprise Records reports that the band was personally invited to participate in the show by Game of Thrones executive producer Dan Weiss, who is a fan of the band.
